{"id":35283,"date":"2021-02-20T11:42:34","date_gmt":"2021-02-20T07:42:34","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=35283"},"modified":"2023-05-30T10:40:28","modified_gmt":"2023-05-30T06:40:28","slug":"munafiq-fajir-kafir-recite","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/02\/20\/munafiq-fajir-kafir-recite\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Hypocrisy: Believers, hypocrites, and evildoers recite Quran"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>There will be successors after sixty years &#8216;who waste the prayer and follow their lusts, so they will soon meet an evil ending&#8217;<\/strong> (19:59). <strong>Then, there will be successors who recite the Quran, but it does not go beyond their throats. There are three who recite the Quran: a believer, a hypocrite, and an evildoer.<\/strong>\u201d Al-Walid said, &#8220;The hypocrite disbelieves in it, the evildoer earns his livelihood from it, and the believer has faith in it.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 11340<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <i>Hasan <\/i>(fair) according to Al-Arna&#8217;ut<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0633\u064e\u0639\u0650\u064a\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064f\u062f\u0652\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0643\u064f\u0648\u0646\u064f \u062e\u064e\u0644\u0652\u0641\u064c \u0628\u064e\u0639\u0652\u062f\u064e \u0633\u0650\u062a\u0651\u0650\u064a\u0646\u064e \u0633\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0629\u064b \u0623\u064e\u0636\u064e\u0627\u0639\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0651\u0